{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place cream, milk, 60 g sugar, egg yolks and vanilla in mixing bowl then cook <b>5 min\/80Â°C\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a freezer-proof container and allow to cool then place in freezer for 3-5 hours or until almost set. Clean mixing bowl and continue with recipe.","Place a saucepan over a high heat on hob then add coconut oil and popcorn kernels. Place lid on and gently shuffle kernels inside saucepan until corn starts popping. Once popping has subsided to 1 pop per second, remove saucepan from heat. Remove lid and sprinkle with salt, to taste. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Line a baking tray with baking paper.","Place remaining 200 g sugar in mixing bowl and grind <b>20 sec\/speed 10<b>.","Transfer to a saucepan and add water. Stir constantly over a high heat for 5-6 minutes or until a golden-brown caramel forms.","Pour half of the caramel over the reserved popcorn and stir through then set aside.","Pour remaining caramel in a thin layer onto prepared baking tray. Allow to set before breaking into shards, then set aside.","Remove ice cream from freezer and cut into 4 cm squares. Place ice cream squares in mixing bowl, crush <b>20 sec\/speed 9<b> then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 6<b>.","Pour ice cream into 6 dariole moulds and add 3-4 pieces of reserved caramel popcorn to each mould. Freeze for 3-4 hours or until set.","Chill serving plates and remove ice cream from freezer 5 minutes before assembly.","Gently remove ice cream from moulds and place on serving plates. Decorate with a few shards of reserved toffee and remaining caramel popcorn then serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["400 g whipping cream","100 g whole milk","260 g sugar","2 egg yolks, from medium eggs","1 tsp vanilla extract","1 tsp coconut oil","20 g popcorn kernels","1 - 4 tsp fine sea salt, to taste","1 Tbsp water"]}],"id":"r134759","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-Zn8y8kVYeEc\/XZWew5fzNVI\/AAAAAAAAe5U\/XObk23vlRmkZGxBpB37jp